1] For Specifically class and id attributes:-

    A class and id are the attributes of a tag used later by the css to style that tag.
    Eg. <div id="" class="first"></div>
    We can reduce our typing time with Emmet abbreviations as:

    1] tagname.classname  => <tagname class=classname> </tagname>
        Eg. <p class="class1"></p>          <!-- Just type p.class1 and enter-->
    2] tagname#idname     => <tagname id=idname> </tagname
        Eg. <h2 id="id1"></h2>              <!-- Just type p#id1 and enter-->
    3] tagname.#idname    => <tagname class="" id=idname> </tagname>
        Eg. <p class="" id="first"></p>     <!--Just type p.#first and enter-->
    4] tagname#.classname => <tagname id="" class="classname"> </tagname>
        Eg. <div id="" class="first"></div> <!--Just type div#.first and enter-->
    5] tagname.classname#idname => <tagname class="classname id="idname"> </tagname>
        Eg. <p class="class1" id="id1"></p> <!--Just type p.class1#id1 and enter-->

2] For custom attributes:-

    For speedy input of just any attribute for a tag, following syntax is used:
        tagname[attributename=""]
        Eg. <p title="List of shops"></p>  <!-- Just type p[title="List of Shops"]-->
    
    For multiple attributes, just enlist them sequentially.
        tagname[attributename1="" attributename2=""]
        Eg. <p class="class1" id="id1"></p> <!--Just type p.class1#id1 and enter-->
    
    For some tags, a few attributes are mandatory.
        Eg.1) <img src="cat.jpg" alt="A cat image"> <!-- Typing img[src="cat.jpg"alt="A cat image"]-->
           2) <img src="" alt="">    <!Typing only img and enter-->
           3) <img src="catalyst.img" alt=""> <!--Tping img[src="catalyst.img"]-->

3] HTML text directly under the tag:-

    Instead of any attributes if one wants to just enter the plain text und an html tag in a shortcut, that can be achieved using following syntax:
        tagname{Content}
        Eg. <p>Hello world!</p>         <!--Typing p{Hello world!} -->
            <h2>Welcome</h2>            <!--Typing h2{Welcome} -->